### Delay Control

Use `delay` to control how long to wait before opening (default: 600ms) and `closeDelay` to control how long to wait before closing (default: 0ms).

<Example demo="tooltip-delay-demo">
  <TooltipDelayDemo />
</Example>

## TooltipProvider

`TooltipProvider` groups multiple tooltips so that after the first tooltip has been shown, switching to another skips the open delay. Place it once at your app root or layout — not around each individual `Tooltip`.

```svelte
<Tooltip.Provider>
  <App />
</Tooltip.Provider>

<Tooltip content="Add">
  {#snippet render({ props })}
    <Button {...props} shape="square" aria-label="Add">+</Button>
  {/snippet}
</Tooltip>
```

## API Reference

### Tooltip

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Inline trigger content. Use this for non-interactive text or icons. |
| `content` | `Snippet \| string` | required | Tooltip content. |
| `render` | `Snippet<{ props }>` | — | Custom trigger render function. Spread `props` onto the real interactive element. |
| `side` | `"top" \| "right" \| "bottom" \| "left"` | `"top"` | Preferred side. |
| `align` | `"start" \| "center" \| "end"` | `"center"` | Alignment along the side. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional content classes. |
| `container` | `PortalProps["to"]` | — | Portal target. |
| `delay` | `number` | `600` | Open delay in milliseconds. |
| `closeDelay` | `number` | `0` | Close delay in milliseconds. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables the tooltip. |

### Tooltip.Provider

| Prop | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | Tooltip subtree. |
| `delayDuration` | `number` | Provider-level open delay. |
| `skipDelayDuration` | `number` | Delay skipped after another tooltip opens. |
| `disableHoverableContent` | `boolean` | Disables hoverable content. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | Disables tooltips in the provider. |

## Svelte Notes

Use the `render` snippet for interactive controls so the tooltip trigger props land on the real button or link. Plain children are still convenient for non-interactive inline text or icons. For lower-level composition, use `TooltipRoot`, `TooltipTrigger`, `TooltipPortal`, and `TooltipContent`.
